<title type="html"><![CDATA[Mustahadah Making Tawaaf of the House of Allah]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=938&amp;p=982#p982"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Question:</span></strong> I (Salih, the son of Imam Ahmad bin Hanbal) asked my father should the Mustahadah make Tawaaf of the house of Allah?<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Response:</span></strong> My Father responded : yes (she should), the Mustahadah’s ruling and condition is that of a clean and pure (women), she should make tawaaf of the house of Allah.<br /><br /><em>Reference: Masaa`il of Imam Ahmed bin Hanbal narrated on the authority of his son Imam Abul-Fadal, Salih bin Imam Ahmad bin Hanbal – Page 236, Issue no: 815</em><br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Footnotes</span></strong><br /><br />[1] Istihadah is the vaginal bleeding of a woman such that it may not stop or it may stop but for a short period of time (a day or two in each month). Refer to Natural Blood of Women, of Sheikh Muhammad bin Salih Uthaymeen (rahimahullaah) English Translation by Dr. Saleh as-Saleh) rahimahullaah), Chapter 5, page 27.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Mon Jan 02, 2017 9:32 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
